benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache - Invalidates the given Cache if specified, otherwise invalidates all caches

covered: Valid Deletion: Scenarios cover deleting all caches (TC01) and specific cache (TC02).
Non-Existent Resource: TC03 covers behavior when cache does not exist.
Unauthorized Access: TC06 covers authentication/authorization failure.
Server Error Handling: TC07 covers system/internal errors resulting in 500.
Empty Response Handling: TC01 and TC08 verify empty response bodies for 204 with no content.
Query Parameters: Multiple scenarios cover various query parameter usages (TC02, TC05, TC11, TC12, TC10).
Performance with Large Dataset: TC13 tests large cache set and response time.
Special Scenarios: TC04 (not alive), TC10 (large cacheName), TC11 (special characters), TC12 (mixed-case) and TC15 (regression) cover edge cases.
gaps: Pagination: No tests verify pagination behavior when listing or handling very large numbers of caches.
Caching Behavior: No tests verify HTTP caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or client-side caching implications.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No tests to validate behavior under rapid successive requests or rate limits.
Soft Deletes: Not applicable to this endpoint, but no explicit confirmation of idempotent/soft-delete semantics beyond 204 could be documented.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling when dealing with large catalogs of caches (e.g., paging through results or performance under paged requests).
Add tests to validate caching headers and client-side caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE responses where applicable.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure stability under bursty traffic.
Consider explicit tests to confirm idempotency and any soft-delete semantics if relevant to the API design, and document any nuances observed during testing.
